<section xml:id="sec-appB-complex-numbers-and-rotations" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Complex numbers and rotations</title>

  <subsection xml:id="appB-cplx-subsec-complex-numbers">
    <title>Complex numbers</title>

    <p>
      <md>\boxed{z=a+bi}</md>
      where
      <md>\boxed{i^2=-1.}</md>
    </p>

    <p>
      Real part:
      <md>\boxed{\operatorname{Re}(a+bi)=a.}</md>
    </p>

    <p>
      Imaginary part:
      <md>\boxed{\operatorname{Im}(a+bi)=b.}</md>
    </p>

    <p>
      Plane point:
      <md>\boxed{a+bi \longleftrightarrow (a,b).}</md>
    </p>
  </subsection>

  <subsection xml:id="appB-cplx-subsec-addition-and-subtraction">
    <title>Addition and subtraction</title>

    <p>
      <md>\boxed{(a+bi)+(c+di)=(a+c)+(b+d)i.}</md>
    </p>

    <p>
      <md>\boxed{(a+bi)-(c+di)=(a-c)+(b-d)i.}</md>
    </p>
  </subsection>

  <subsection xml:id="appB-cplx-subsec-multiplication">
    <title>Multiplication</title>

    <p>
      <md>\boxed{(a+bi)(c+di)=(ac-bd)+(ad+bc)i.}</md>
    </p>

    <p>
      Multiplication by <m>i</m>:
      <md>\boxed{i(a+bi)=-b+ai.}</md>
    </p>

    <p>
      As a plane rotation:
      <md>\boxed{(a,b)\mapsto(-b,a).}</md>
      This is a <m>90^\circ</m> counterclockwise rotation.
    </p>
  </subsection>

  <subsection xml:id="appB-cplx-subsec-conjugate">
    <title>Conjugate</title>

    <p>
      <md>\boxed{\overline{a+bi}=a-bi.}</md>
    </p>

    <p>
      Geometrically, conjugation reflects across the real axis:
      <md>(a,b)\mapsto(a,-b).</md>
    </p>
  </subsection>

  <subsection xml:id="appB-cplx-subsec-modulus">
    <title>Modulus</title>

    <p>
      <md>\boxed{|a+bi|=\sqrt{a^2+b^2}.}</md>
    </p>

    <p>
      <md>\boxed{z\overline z=|z|^2.}</md>
    </p>
  </subsection>

  <subsection xml:id="appB-cplx-subsec-division">
    <title>Division</title>

    <p>
      To divide by
      <md>c+di,</md>
      multiply top and bottom by
      <md>c-di.</md>
    </p>

    <p>
      <md>\boxed{\frac{a+bi}{c+di} = \frac{(a+bi)(c-di)}{c^2+d^2}}</md>
      for
      <md>c+di\ne0.</md>
    </p>
  </subsection>

  <subsection xml:id="appB-cplx-subsec-polar-form">
    <title>Polar form</title>

    <p>
      If
      <md>z=a+bi\ne0,</md>
      then
      <md>\boxed{z=r(\cos\theta+i\sin\theta)}</md>
      where
      <md>\boxed{r=|z|=\sqrt{a^2+b^2}.}</md>
    </p>

    <p>
      The angle <m>\theta</m> satisfies
      <md>\cos\theta=\frac ar, \qquad \sin\theta=\frac br.</md>
    </p>
  </subsection>

  <subsection xml:id="appB-cplx-subsec-multiplication-in-polar-form">
    <title>Multiplication in polar form</title>

    <p>
      If
      <md>z=r(\cos\alpha+i\sin\alpha),</md>
      and
      <md>w=s(\cos\beta+i\sin\beta),</md>
      then
      <md>\boxed{zw = rs\bigl(\cos(\alpha+\beta)+i\sin(\alpha+\beta)\bigr).}</md>
    </p>

    <p>
      Complex multiplication:
      <md>\boxed{\text{multiplies lengths and adds angles.}}</md>
    </p>
  </subsection>

  <subsection xml:id="appB-cplx-subsec-de-moivres-formula">
    <title>De Moivre's formula</title>

    <p>
      <md>\boxed{\bigl(r(\cos\theta+i\sin\theta)\bigr)^n = r^n(\cos(n\theta)+i\sin(n\theta)).}</md>
    </p>

    <p>
      For unit complex numbers:
      <md>\boxed{(\cos\theta+i\sin\theta)^n = \cos(n\theta)+i\sin(n\theta).}</md>
    </p>
  </subsection>

  <warning xml:id="appB-cplx-warning-common-warnings">
    <title>Common warnings</title>
    <p>
      The number <m>0</m> has no polar angle.
    </p>
    <p>
      Angles in polar form are not unique:
      <md>\theta \quad\text{and}\quad \theta+2\pi k</md>
      describe the same direction.
    </p>
    <p>
      Complex multiplication is not componentwise multiplication:
      <md>(a,b)(c,d)\ne(ac,bd).</md>
    </p>
  </warning>
</section>
